        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 8 at 9:11AM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 911 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles south of Greenwood, moving east at 60 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Greenwood, Ninety Six, Troy, Ninety Six Historic Site, Greenwood
State Park, Promised Land, Bradley, Kirksey, Callison, and Epworth.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
